cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for object recognition in videos using convolutional recurrent neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Winner-Take-All dropout and autoencoders also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for initializing and regularizing the networks, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
